{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Make 1 batch quick puff pastry (see tip).","Preheat oven to 180°C and line 2 baking trays with baking paper.","Place sugar and almonds in mixing bowl then grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Add butter and mix <b>6 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.","On a lightly-floured surface, roll chilled pastry out to a square (approx. 32 cm), then trim edges so pastry measures 30 cm x 30 cm. Cut into 9 squares (10 cm) then transfer to prepared trays, 3 cm apart.","Place 1 tsp reserved almond mixture in centre of each pastry square. Make a cut from each corner into centre then fold alternate corners into centre and press down gently. Brush pastry with beaten egg then top each with an apricot half.","Bake for 15-18 minutes (180°C) until puffed and golden.","While still hot, brush apricot halves with apricot glaze then leave to cool before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["490 g quick puff pastry, homemade","50 g granulated sugar","50 g blanched almonds","50 g unsalted butter, soft","plain flour, for dusting","1 medium egg, beaten","9 tinned apricot halves, drained","30 g apricot jam, mixed with 1 tsp hot water, for glazing"]}],"id":"r132990","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-0aItpe7KUjk\/XZWp8M3YWZI\/AAAAAAAAfQ4\/imG_E-eVOlsxOsQ-BXOKfsld_9uLvJmZQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_8SLZTt79qZ0IwNaw.png","title":"Apricot Danish Pastries","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.5 g","fat":"8.4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"13.7 g","calories":"590 kJ \/ 141 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking trays and baking paper, rolling pin, pastry brush, oven","hintsAndTricks":["You’re unlikely to buy pastries again once you discover how easy it is to make your own. This flaky pastry is nicely complemented by the gooey, nutty, apricot centre.","For a quick puff pastry recipe refer to the recipe in <i>Sweet - Cakes, Bakes and Teatime Treats<\/i> on Cookidoo®."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","40m","9 pieces"]}